<div class="prose-content max-w-3xl">

  <p>The Pharmacy First Scotland service means your pharmacist can assess and treat a range of everyday conditions on the NHS. You don't need to see a GP first — just walk in to your local pharmacy.</p>

  <h2>Conditions treated under Pharmacy First</h2>

  <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-3 mb-6 not-prose">
    {% set conditions = [
      "Urinary tract infection (UTI) in women aged 16–65",
      "Impetigo (skin infection)",
      "Shingles",
      "Sinusitis",
      "Sore throat",
      "Earache in children aged 1–17",
      "Infected insect bites",
      "Minor eye conditions (conjunctivitis)",
      "Headlice treatment",
      "Oral thrush"
    ] %}
    {% for condition in conditions %}
    <div class="flex items-start gap-2 bg-brand-light rounded p-3 text-sm">
      <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="w-5 h-5 text-brand-primary flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor" aria-hidden="true">
        <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M4.5 12.75l6 6 9-13.5"/>
      </svg>
      <span>{{ condition }}</span>
    </div>
    {% endfor %}
  </div>

  <h2>How to use Pharmacy First</h2>
  <ol>
    <li>Visit or call your local pharmacy.</li>
    <li>Tell them you'd like to use the Pharmacy First service.</li>
    <li>The pharmacist will assess your condition.</li>
    <li>They may be able to treat you there and then, or refer you to another service if needed.</li>
  </ol>
  <p>The service is free of charge on the NHS. You do not need a prescription or referral from us.</p>

  <h2>Find a local pharmacy</h2>
  <p>Use the <a href="https://www.nhsinform.scot/scotlands-service-directory/pharmacy" rel="noopener noreferrer">NHS Inform pharmacy finder</a> to find a pharmacy near you.</p>

</div>
